                        <p>“He just looks really active out there. He’s just really working out how to use his length and athleticism to block shots and come over,” Duke captain Jack White said. “You saw tonight, he just affects so many plays in different ways and he’s all over the court rebounding and running the floor.”</p>
<p>After some turmoil, it seems as though Krzyzewski has found his fifth starter for good. As long as he avoids the lower-body injuries that have nagged him for the last three years, Bolden should continue his breakout campaign and provide a menacing defensive presence for the Blue Devils.</p>

